      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just don't see why the \"resistance\" thing is such a big deal for just one small skin infection on my arm. it feels like doctors just prescribe a standard amount for everyone regardless of how they actually respond. if i can see with my own eyes that the skin is perfectly normal and there's zero swelling, isn't it more logical to stop once the symptoms are gone? i'd rather avoid the risk of side effects from the meds than risk some theoretical resistance issue.",
